    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="from">Chiang</persName> to President
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d106fn1">Sent by <persName corresp="#p_SJW1"
                            >Stilwell</persName>, via Army channels, in telegram 858, November 9,
                        1943, which was marked as “Secret”, “Priority”, and “For the eyes of Gen
                            <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">Marshall</persName> only for transmission to
                        the President”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-09">9 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mme <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> down with flu and dysentery.
                    Funeral of late President <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Lin Sen</persName>
                    scheduled for 17th. Provided Mme <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName>
                    has recovered I intend to leave here early on the 18th. Otherwise I must delay
                    my departure, in which case your conference with <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName> can take place before ours. I prefer seeing you before
                    you see <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> and sincerely hope our
                    plans will work out in that way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chiang Kai-shek</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
